{"id":"taches","term":"Taches","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Hooks or clasps by which the tabernacle curtains were connected (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 26:6\">Ex. 26:6</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 26:11\">11</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 2:2\">33</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 35:11\">35:11</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Exodus 26:6","Exodus 26:11","Genesis 2:2","Genesis 35:11"]}